nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So if East opened 3@C, we end up in 4@S for down 1 or perhaps even in 4@H which is down a huge amount with the 5-0 break. One thing to keep in mind when there is a preempt you should be more reluctant to play in a 4-4 fit because the odds of a 4-1 break are much higher than normal.|
PG| ***** 53 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Normally the odds of a 3-2 break are around 2/3 (68% actually). But after a preempt they probably go down to around 60% or even less.|
PG| ***** 54 ***** |


