PG| ***** 55 ***** |


cp|8|AT|^^
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|For two reasons East is not correct. Here we don't make 4@S and if we do make 4@S, we are likely to be bidding it even without a preempt. So the preempt doesn't "push us" anywhere,|
PG| ***** 56 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There are hands where we might end up bidding game after a preempt that we might not bid otherwise, but only rarely. But there are many more hands where we will end up in the wrong spot, not high enough, too high, or in the wrong suit.|
PG| ***** 57 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The advantages of preempting far outweigh the disadvantages.|
